title: Relativity Space Scrubs Maiden Flight Of Terran 1 Rocket
summary: On 8th March 2023, Relativity Space scrubbed the Good Luck Have Fun (GLHF) launch due to exceeding launch commit criteria levels for the thermal conditions of Stage 2.

title: Relativity Space scrubs launch of 3D-printed, methane-fueled orbital rocket
summary: Relativity Space, a California-based startup that counts billionaire Mark Cuban as one of its early investors, called off the first launch attempt for its 3D-printed, methane-fueled rocket at Cape Canaveral Wednesday.

title: NASA, Smithsonian to Discuss Air Quality Satellite Instrument
summary: Media are invited to a joint briefing with NASA and The Smithsonian Astrophysical Observatory at 9 a.m. EDT Tuesday, March 14, to discuss the first space-based instrument to observe major air pollutants across North America every hour during the daytime.

title: Relativity postpones first launch attempt of 3D-printed rocket Terran 1
summary: 3D-printing specialist Relativity Space postponed its first launch attempt on Wednesday, a mission that marks the most significant test yet of the company’s ambitious manufacturing approach.

title: U.S. Space Force game plan: Compete with China, prevent shooting war in orbit
summary: In the space domain, the plan is to be in a state of “perpetual competition" with rival powers, said Gen. B. Chance Saltzman, chief of space operations of the U.S. Space Force.
